<db:section xml:id="details">
<db:title>Detailed Description</db:title>
<db:para>Inline images are represented by a Unicode value U+FFFC (OBJECT REPLACEMENT CHARACTER) which has an associated <db:link xlink:href="qtextimageformat.xml">QTextImageFormat</db:link>. The image format specifies a name with <db:link xlink:href="qtextimageformat.xml#setName">setName</db:link>() that is used to locate the image. The size of the rectangle that the image will occupy is specified using <db:link xlink:href="qtextimageformat.xml#setWidth">setWidth</db:link>() and <db:link xlink:href="qtextimageformat.xml#setHeight">setHeight</db:link>().</db:para>
<db:para>Images can be supplied in any format for which Qt has an image reader, so SVG drawings can be included alongside PNG, TIFF and other bitmap formats.</db:para>
